cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.DL (Digital Libraries) as it focuses on bibliometric analysis of scientific publications. It could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it studies international collaboration among researchers and their performance. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as it may discuss the impact of political events on scientific development. Finally, it could be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it uses software tools to analyze data from the Science Citation Index.
